sentences: Fred Welton Warmsley III (born September 22, 1987 (formerly Lee Bannon), is an American record producer and sound artist from Sacramento, California.

Initially known for his work with the New York City-based hip hop collective Pro Era, he has since been known for producing in multiple genres including breakcore, ambient and noise music, releasing eight extended plays and two long plays since 2013, including the critically acclaimed Alternate/Endings.
His debut studio album under the name Dedekind Cut, entitled $uccessor, was released in November 2016.
